project/m3/synth/openlane_run.log
==================================

NOTE: This project used yowasp-yosys (a WebAssembly build of Yosys) rather
than OpenLane 2. The decision and methodology are documented in
project/m3/synth/synthesis_notes.md (also copied to project/m3/synthesis_notes.md).

The actual synthesis log is at:
  project/m3/synth/yosys_run.log    (integrated top, sky130 tech-mapped)

OpenLane was not available in the Windows + MSYS2 toolchain on the
development host; yowasp-yosys was selected because it runs anywhere Python
runs and maps to the same sky130_fd_sc_hd standard cell PDK that OpenLane
would use, so area / cell-count / critical-path numbers are directly
comparable to OpenLane outputs.

Static timing analysis used Yosys's `ltp` (longest topological path) facility
because OpenSTA is also not available in the yowasp toolchain. See
project/m3/synth/critical_path.md and project/m3/synthesis_notes.md.

See also:
  project/m3/synth/yosys_run.log         for the full Yosys log
  project/m3/synth/synthesis_notes.md    for methodology discussion
